{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Allergy law should require PAL, cosmetic labeling and clear cosmetic ingredients",
        "additional_details": "I believe these changes to the law will save lives.\r\nPrecautionary allergen labelling (eg. May contain...) is not currently required on products, it needs to be legally required on ALL products, food & non-food, & toiletries, cosmetics etc \r\nSecondly, cosmetics, toiletries etc. don't have to declare the 14 major allergens that food products do, this needs to change. \r\nFinally, cosmetic products need to include the common name of a product, not just the Latin name (eg Arachis hypogaea aka Peanuts)",
        "background": "I want the current laws updated or a new law that contains:\r\nPrecautionary allergen labelling (eg. May contain...) on ALL products, food and non-food\r\nCosmetics, toiletries etc. must follow the same allergen laws as food\r\nCosmetics must not only use Latin names etc. but also the common names",
